    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Repress Yourself</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anne Schettino Casale letter praises idea of repression of trauma (Feb 23 Lauren Slater article) and finds things come to surface as she is ready to deal with them</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was delighted to read the article. It has been my experience that when I am ready to deal with an issue I have repressed, the problem manages to swim to the surface and make itself known.</p>
        <p>For the rest, I have been content to deal by not dealing, and certainly I have no intention of fishing in murky waters to see what is surely better left alone.</p>
        <p>Anne Schettino Casale  Trenton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
